          \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-ring-08.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-ring-08.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-ring-08.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-ring-08.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                \u003cimg width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A gold Samsung Galaxy Ring resting vertically on the edge of a wooden table\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-ring-08.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/samsung-galaxy-ring-08.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-samsung-galaxy-ring\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Samsung Galaxy Ring?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eSamsung really hit it out of the park with its first smart ring, delivering a product that does most things you need without any added costs like a subscription service. The Galaxy Ring feels good on the finger, and the premium materials allow it to stand out from other smart rings produced by some competitors.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eWhile it\u0026#39;s not much to look at, it does deliver when it comes to health and fitness tracking, although we do wish it did more in the latter category. As far as battery life goes, you can expect up to seven days, which is quite good for such a small device. The cool part is that it comes with a charging case, which makes it possible to charge while on the go.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eOf course, durability is also a big part of the Galaxy Ring, offering ample protection against dust and moisture. So you can feel confident taking it with you on a long hike, or just hopping in the shower in the morning. But what makes the ring more appealing now is the special promotion from Samsung that allows you to trade in a device to save up to $250.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eAs far as what you can trade in, it\u0026#39;s a bit limited, but Samsung is accepting smart rings and smartwatches. So be sure to head to the \u003ca href=\"https://howl.link/zk4bwtfr4i1tn\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSamsung website to see what your device is valued at\u003c/a\u003e and if it\u0026#39;s worth trading in. The maximum Samsung is offering is $250, which is quite good. But you\u0026#39;ll want to be quick because this promotion won\u0026#39;t be around for that long.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
